posts.name: Nicholas Armstrong
posts.cooked: When using a Neural Network detection pipeline how do you get the name of the object detected in PhotonLib.  Which method provides it?

posts.name: viggy96
posts.cooked:
Could be wrong but I think the fiducial ID method gives you the ID of the item. And each item in the model will have its own ID integer, 0, 1, 2 etc. There’s a text file that maps the items in the model to integers.

It can’t give you the name directly.

posts.name: viggy96
posts.cooked: @bankst Can chime in here with a smarter answer than mine.

posts.name: Nicholas Armstrong
posts.cooked: So having my own map from integer to name/enum wouldn’t hurt.

posts.name: viggy96
posts.cooked: Yeah, that’s a simple way of doing things.

posts.name: Nicholas Armstrong
posts.cooked: In the latest 2025 beta PhotonTrackedId has objDetectId and objDetectConf

posts.name: Nicholas Armstrong
posts.cooked:
Also I created a PhotonVisionCamera wrapper object that integrates the examples from their repo/website.
